            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Documentation was lacking. This PR proposes to add:\r\n\r\n    For `height`, a decimal number smaller than 1 is a fraction of 'lines'.\r\n\r\nDoes this help in addition to that?\r\n\r\n    For full height use `height = 0.999`, to limit to one line use `height = 1`.",
            "commit_id": "8f8c30efbe86524e7856d21e3e6ccd885fd08d5c",
            "created_at": "2026-05-14T12:38:16Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -608,8 +612,9 @@ end\n local was_cmdwin = ''\n ---@param min integer Minimum window height.\n local function win_row_height_border(tgt, min)\n-  local cfgmin = ui.cfg.msg[tgt].height --[[@as number]]\n-  min = math.min(min, cfgmin > 1 and cfgmin or math.ceil(o.lines * cfgmin))\n+  local cfgmin = tonumber(ui.cfg.msg[tgt].height)\n+  local frac = cfgmin <= 1 and ui.cfg.msg[tgt].height:find('%.')",
